  "title": "Pericardium",
  "body_html": "<div>The pericardium has an outer fibrous layer and inner serous layer. The serous layer is further split into parietal and visceral layers with a pericardial space in between that contains pericardial fluid.<br /><br />The parietal layer is fused to the fibrous pericardium whilst the visceral pericardium can be considered part of the epicardium.<br /><br /><i>Image illustrating the layers of the pericardium</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb083b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb083.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pericardium'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb083b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><b>Innervation</b><br /><ul><li>Fibrous pericardium and the parietal layer of serous pericardium are supplied by phrenic nerves. </li><li>Visceral layer of serous pericardium is innervated by branches of sympathetic trunks and vagus nerves.</li></ul></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>Patient.co.uk</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_66\" data-linkid=\"66\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_66\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\